===Gershayim===
{{main|Gershayim}}
The symbol {{Hebrew|'''״'''}} is called a [[gershayim]] and is a punctuation mark used in the Hebrew language to denote acronyms. It is written before the last letter in the acronym, e.g. {{Hebrew|ר״ת}}. Gershayim is also the name of a note of [[cantillation]] in the reading of the [[Torah]], printed above the accented letter, e.g. {{Hebrew|א֞}}.

